node.text:
It’s quite telling when even #CNN turns on #JoeBiden and calls him a foreign policy failure. All you had to do was look at his past. In the Obama admin, every general said that Joe has been on the wrong side of every single foreign policy decision for the last few DECADES. They were all right, and now we have even more proof. 

 #JakeTapper: We are “watching a tragic foreign policy disaster unfold before our eyes...The rapid crumbling of #Afghanistan has caught the #Biden #WhiteHouse flat footed.”

“It seems shocking that President Biden could’ve been so wrong” 

#SleepyJoe #KamalaHarris #Comeonman

node.title: Jake Tapper: We‘re “Watching a Tragic Foreign Policy Disaster Unfold …”

node.text: #Florida Governor (and future President) #RonDeSantis completely takes apart #JoeBiden on his failed handling of the border and his failure to lead on a myriad of issues.  This comes after the Biden administration told #DeSantis to “get out of the way” on Covid. How do Democrats not see that having an open border, especially right now, is a really bad idea?  Aren’t they trying to lower infections?  Just a guess but having an open border probably isn’t going to help with that…

node.title: FL Gov. Ron DeSantis Destroys Joe Biden on Covid & Southern Border

“Are you saying that #OAN is not a credible news source?”

… Saying OAN is not credible is pretty funny coming from CNN …

node.text: #JoeBiden has publicly spoken twice since #Afghanistan fell to the #Taliban under his watch. Both times this past Monday, and today, he flees immediately after his prepared remarks on the teleprompter.  Twice in a row he ran away from the press at a time when so many questions have to be answered … 🏃 Way to go, Joe! i think at this point, we see the back of his head more than the front. That’s “leadership”, folks. 👏🏼 #PresidentTrump would have stayed for an hour and half and taken questions from everyone in the room — assuming he would even be in this situation. 45 would have handled this with true leadership.  #comeonman #sleepyjoe #sloppyjoe

node.text:
“Do you have the ability to go out and collect Americans?”

#SecretaryofDefense Austin: “We don't have the capability to go out and collect large numbers of people.” … sounds to me like #JoeBiden made his recent decision without consulting with any generals.  I don’t think any of them would have done it this way. I think most would agree that we needed to leave #Afghanistan. #PresidentTrump was making preparations to do so. That’s not the issue. The problem is that it was done so sloppily, unnecessarily putting so many at risk. Now we need approval from the Taliban to get our people out? That’s pretty sad.

node.text:
Afghan reporter #NaziraKarimi gets very emotional during #Pentagon briefing:

"I'm very upset today because Afghan women didn't expect overnight that all the #Taliban came. They took off my flag-this is my flag-they put their flag. Everybody is upset...Where is my president?!" Wow. You can feel the utter frustration in her voice. Could #JoeBiden really not do any better?  I think most people were in agreement that we should leave #Afghanistan but there is a good, bad and terrible way to do that and it’s unfortunate #SleepyJoe chose the latter.

node.text: Here’s what we heard from the #Biden admin over the last couple weeks and days about #Afghanistan. But fear not America, because #SleepyJoe will be cutting his vacation short today, coming back to the #WhiteHouse and addressing the nation at 12:45 PST / 3:45 EST. #comeonman

node.text: Chaotic scene at #Kabul #InternationalAirport. No security anywhere to be seen.  Looks like people are desperately trying to get out of #Afghanistan. This will likely turn into another refugee crisis for Europe … and yeah, America. #JoeBiden and #KamalaHarris will open the border even wider to make room for the another problem they helped create. How much did we spend in that country? 150 billion? Not really sure what we got out of it. Money well spent, right? #comeonman
